-- B y  
-- 
2011-05-23T04:07:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/france-daybook-sarkozy-makes-speech-on-labor-globalization.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy 
makes a speech on labor and globalization at a Group of 20
nations ministers’ meeting in Paris.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
*  Industry Minister Eric Besson meeting with Spanish
counterpart, discussing power transportation.  ECONOMY:
* 09:00 French May PMI Manufacturing, Services  GOVERNMENT:
* 09:30 President Sarkozy Makes Speech to G-20 Labor Ministers
* 10:15 Finance Minister Lagarde Joins Panel at G-20 Ministers
Conference
* 11:45 Energy Minister Eric Besson meets counterparts in
Madrid Visits
* 12:15 Finance Minister Lagarde Signs French-Austrian Fiscal
Agreement
* 14:40 Prime Minister Fillon Visits Senoble Factory in Central
France  EQUITIES:
*The CAC 40 Index fell 36.89, or 0.9 percent, to 3,990.85.
*The broader SBF 120 Index dropped 0.8 percent.  MARKETS:
* Ingenico SA (ING FO) VeriFone Systems Inc., Hypercom Corp and
Ingenico have abandoned plans for Hypercom to divest its U.S.
point-of-sale business to Ingenico, the U.S. Justice Department
said in a statement.
* Suez Environnement SA (SEV FP) may be fined next week by the
European Union for breaking a seal regulators attached to an
office door during an antitrust raid last year, two people with
knowledge of the matter said.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
